Subject: Re: [T2] flywheel seal

At 02:51 PM 08/14/2002, you wrote:
>  now i have a pretty major oil leak from between the eng. and trans. 
> (flywheel seal).  i need to know is there some trick to replacing this 
> seal? i dont want to have to re re do it.

Be sure to polish the seal surface on the flywheel. It could also be 
leaking from the trans mainshaft seal.

>  i also want to know how to check the end play while i have the flywheel 
> off again.

No, you must check the end play before removing the flywheel, then remove 
it and measure the shims, then put in the proper shim calculated from the 
measurement.


